import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    S = []
    
    # Add points along a diagonal, which are guaranteed to be non-collinear. Then, try to add other points.
    for i in range(n):
        S.append((i, (i*i) % n)) # Quadratic residues are good for no-three-in-line.
        
    # Remove duplicate points from S, if any
    S = list(set(S))
    
    return S
